# Component Builder Skill

## Purpose
Create reusable UI components in a structured, scalable, and consistent way using modern frontend practices.

## Inputs
- Component name
- Props definition
- UI requirements (design or description)
- Styling approach (e.g. Tailwind)

## Outputs
- A fully functional component file
- Clean folder structure
- Typed props (TypeScript)
- Exported component ready for use

## Steps
1. Create a new folder under `/components/<ComponentName>`
2. Create the main file: `<ComponentName>.tsx`
3. Define TypeScript interface for props
4. Build component UI using semantic HTML
5. Apply styling (Tailwind or chosen system)
6. Add basic accessibility (labels, roles if needed)
7. Export the component as default
8. (Optional) Add index.ts for cleaner imports

## Rules
- Use PascalCase for component names
- Keep components small and focused (single responsibility)
- Do not mix business logic inside UI components
- Always type props (no `any`)
- Prefer functional components with hooks
- Ensure accessibility basics are covered

## Example
/components/Button/Button.tsx
```tsx
type ButtonProps = {
  label: string;
  onClick: () => void;
};

export default function Button({ label, onClick }: ButtonProps) {
  return (
    <button onClick={onClick} className="px-4 py-2 bg-black text-white">
      {label}
    </button>
  );
}